    <item>
      <title>One of the most beautiful exhibitions I’ve seen in a long time — L’Empire du som...</title>
      <link>https://www.instagram.com/p/DTsB3gojV7_/</link>
      <description><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.71878-15/619765738_1149774400361091_3876132327877190145_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_p360x360_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=110&amp;ig_cache_key=MzgxMzQzMTE5NzEzMzc5MDk3NQ%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjY0MHgxMTM2LnNkci5DMyJ9&amp;_nc_ohc=T2gAsHGzN18Q7kNvwFaoP5k&amp;_nc_oc=AdpiAmqKtv-v53sX6Cjfpm9XTFp7olUM_YpUpi1uVhfxoju9DEYyF7YZdXh9hq-5Chk&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=pnWVVDrzlyS15aUSdqm7YA&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_Afwi8ZLot7WM3CcXlQBVDoLM-v79RNuLeXJ6cYZB4SDlPg&amp;oe=69C8EA8D" alt="Instagram billede fra @balder_olrik" /></p><p><strong>@balder_olrik</strong></p><p>One of the most beautiful exhibitions I’ve seen in a long time — L’Empire du sommeil at the Musée Marmottan Monet  (16th arrondissement, metro La Muette). 🌙<br/>
A quiet, dreamlike journey through how painters have imagined sleep:  from Goya’s nightmares to Füssli’s strange visions, Sorolla’s luminous rest, Previati’s soft reveries, and the oneiric worlds of Picasso, Grandville, and Klinger.<br/>
Every room felt like a different kind of sleep — unsettling, tender, or suspended somewhere between night and waking.<br/>
 On view until March 1, 2026.  If you’re in Paris, don’t miss it. ✨</p>]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="https://scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.71878-15/619765738_1149774400361091_3876132327877190145_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_p360x360_tt6&amp;_nc_cat=110&amp;ig_cache_key=MzgxMzQzMTE5NzEzMzc5MDk3NQ%3D%3D.3-ccb7-5&amp;ccb=7-5&amp;_nc_sid=58cdad&amp;efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6InhwaWRzLjY0MHgxMTM2LnNkci5DMyJ9&amp;_nc_ohc=T2gAsHGzN18Q7kNvwFaoP5k&amp;_nc_oc=AdpiAmqKtv-v53sX6Cjfpm9XTFp7olUM_YpUpi1uVhfxoju9DEYyF7YZdXh9hq-5Chk&amp;_nc_ad=z-m&amp;_nc_cid=0&amp;_nc_zt=23&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-cph2-1.cdninstagram.com&amp;_nc_gid=pnWVVDrzlyS15aUSdqm7YA&amp;_nc_ss=7a338&amp;oh=00_Afwi8ZLot7WM3CcXlQBVDoLM-v79RNuLeXJ6cYZB4SDlPg&amp;oe=69C8EA8D" alt="Instagram billede fra @balder_olrik" /></p><p><strong>@balder_olrik</strong></p><p>One of the most beautiful exhibitions I’ve seen in a long time — L’Empire du sommeil at the Musée Marmottan Monet  (16th arrondissement, metro La Muette). 🌙<br/>
A quiet, dreamlike journey through how painters have imagined sleep:  from Goya’s nightmares to Füssli’s strange visions, Sorolla’s luminous rest, Previati’s soft reveries, and the oneiric worlds of Picasso, Grandville, and Klinger.<br/>
Every room felt like a different kind of sleep — unsettling, tender, or suspended somewhere between night and waking.<br/>
 On view until March 1, 2026.  If you’re in Paris, don’t miss it. ✨</p>]]></content:encoded>
